COLOR. Body black (
Fig. 5e
). Antennal flagellum without a white band, brown apically. Face and postscutellum yellow with black marking medially, but sometimes entirely black except for inner margin of eye. Clypeus, subalar prominence, propodeum, fore and mid legs, hind trochanter, hind trochantellus, apex of hind femur, and apex of T1 yellow. Fore wing with an apical dark mark extending downwards (
Fig. 4e
).

Subgenital plate pentagonal with basal angle obtuse (
